    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Magnetic Pickup</title>
        <para>A magnetic pickup sensor generates an alternating frequency that indicates speed. Magnetic pickup sensors
            normally have two wire connections for signal and ground. The magnetic pickup sensor has a permanent
            magnetic core surrounded by a wire coil. The signal frequency is generated by the rotation of gear teeth
            that disturb the magnetic field created by the magnet. Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1750123">Vehicle Speed Sensor (Magnetic Pickup)
                <xref refid="f1750123"/>.
            </hotlnk>
        </para>
